<div class="c140_4">
<div id="v140.4.1"><span class="H6213 s">Moreover he made</span><span class="H4196 s"> an altar</span><span class="H5178 s"> of brass</span><span class="H6242 s">, twenty</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H753 s"> the length</span><span class="H6242 s"> thereof, and twenty</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H7341 s"> the breadth</span><span class="H6235 s"> thereof, and ten</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H6967 s"> the height</span> thereof.</div>
<div id="v140.4.2"><span class="H6213 s">Also he made</span><span class="H3332 s"> a molten</span><span class="H3220 s"> sea</span><span class="H6235 s"> of ten</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H8193 s"> from brim</span><span class="H8193 s"> to brim</span><span class="H5696 s">, round</span><span class="H5439 s"> in compass</span><span class="H2568 s">, and five</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H6967 s"> the height</span><span class="H6957 s"> thereof; and a line</span><span class="H7970 s"> of thirty</span><span class="H520 s"> cubits</span><span class="H5437 s"> did compass</span><span class="H5439 s"> it round about</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (from…: Heb. from his brim to his brim)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.3"><span class="H1823 s">And under it <i>was</i> the similitude</span><span class="H1241 s"> of oxen</span><span class="H5437 s">, which did compass</span><span class="H5439 s"> it round about</span><span class="H6235 s">: ten</span><span class="H520 s"> in a cubit</span><span class="H5362 s">, compassing</span><span class="H3220 s"> the sea</span><span class="H5439 s"> round about</span><span class="H8147 s">. Two</span><span class="H2905 s"> rows</span><span class="H1241 s"> of oxen</span><span class="H3332 s"> <i>were</i> cast</span><span class="H4166 s">, when it was cast</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.4"><span class="H5975 s">It stood</span><span class="H8147 s"> upon twelve</span><span class="H6240 s"> †</span><span class="H1241 s"> oxen</span><span class="H7969 s">, three</span><span class="H6437 s"> looking</span><span class="H6828 s"> toward the north</span><span class="H7969 s">, and three</span><span class="H6437 s"> looking</span><span class="H3220 s"> toward the west</span><span class="H7969 s">, and three</span><span class="H6437 s"> looking</span><span class="H5045 s"> toward the south</span><span class="H7969 s">, and three</span><span class="H6437 s"> looking</span><span class="H4217 s"> toward the east</span><span class="H3220 s">: and the sea</span><span class="H4605 s"> <i>was set</i> above</span><span class="H268 s"> upon them, and all their hinder parts</span><span class="H1004 s"> <i>were</i> inward</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.5"><span class="H5672 s">And the thickness</span><span class="H2947 s"> of it <i>was</i> an handbreadth</span><span class="H8193 s">, and the brim</span><span class="H4639 s"> of it like the work</span><span class="H8193 s"> of the brim</span><span class="H3563 s"> of a cup</span><span class="H6525 s">, with flowers</span><span class="H7799 s"> of lilies</span><span class="H2388 s">; <i>and</i> it received</span><span class="H3557 s"> and held</span><span class="H7969 s"> three</span><span class="H505 s"> thousand</span><span class="H1324 s"> baths</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (with flowers…: or, like a lilyflower)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.6"><span class="H6213 s">He made</span><span class="H6235 s"> also ten</span><span class="H3595 s"> lavers</span><span class="H5414 s">, and put</span><span class="H2568 s"> five</span><span class="H3225 s"> on the right hand</span><span class="H2568 s">, and five</span><span class="H8040 s"> on the left</span><span class="H7364 s">, to wash</span><span class="H4639 s"> in them: such things as they offered</span><span class="H5930 s"> for the burnt offering</span><span class="H1740 s"> they washed</span><span class="H3220 s"> in them; but the sea</span><span class="H3548 s"> <i>was</i> for the priests</span><span class="H7364 s"> to wash in</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (such…: Heb. the work of burnt offering)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.7"><span class="H6213 s">And he made</span><span class="H6235 s"> ten</span><span class="H4501 s"> candlesticks</span><span class="H2091 s"> of gold</span><span class="H4941 s"> according to their form</span><span class="H5414 s">, and set</span><span class="H1964 s"> <i>them</i> in the temple</span><span class="H2568 s">, five</span><span class="H3225 s"> on the right hand</span><span class="H2568 s">, and five</span><span class="H8040 s"> on the left</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.8"><span class="H6213 s">He made</span><span class="H6235 s"> also ten</span><span class="H7979 s"> tables</span><span class="H3240 s">, and placed</span><span class="H1964 s"> <i>them</i> in the temple</span><span class="H2568 s">, five</span><span class="H3225 s"> on the right side</span><span class="H2568 s">, and five</span><span class="H8040 s"> on the left</span><span class="H6213 s">. And he made</span><span class="H3967 s"> an hundred</span><span class="H4219 s"> basons</span><span class="H2091 s"> of gold</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (basons: or, bowls)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.9"><span class="H6213 s">Furthermore he made</span><span class="H2691 s"> the court</span><span class="H3548 s"> of the priests</span><span class="H1419 s">, and the great</span><span class="H5835 s"> court</span><span class="H1817 s">, and doors</span><span class="H5835 s"> for the court</span><span class="H6823 s">, and overlaid</span><span class="H1817 s"> the doors</span><span class="H5178 s"> of them with brass</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.10"><span class="H5414 s">And he set</span><span class="H3220 s"> the sea</span><span class="H3233 s"> on the right</span><span class="H3802 s"> side</span><span class="H6924 s"> of the east end</span><span class="H4136 s">, over against</span><span class="H5045 s"> the south</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.11"><span class="H2361 s">And Huram</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H5518 s"> the pots</span><span class="H3257 s">, and the shovels</span><span class="H4219 s">, and the basons</span><span class="H2361 s">. And Huram</span><span class="H2438 s"> †</span><span class="H3615 s"> finished</span><span class="H6213 s"> †</span><span class="H4399 s"> the work</span><span class="H6213 s"> that he was to make</span><span class="H4428 s"> for king</span><span class="H8010 s"> Solomon</span><span class="H1004 s"> for the house</span><span class="H430 s"> of God</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (basons: or, bowls) (finished: Heb. finished to make)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.12"><span class="H8147 s"><i>To wit</i>, the two</span><span class="H5982 s"> pillars</span><span class="H1543 s">, and the pommels</span><span class="H3805 s">, and the chapiters</span><span class="H7218 s"> <i>which were</i> on the top</span><span class="H5982 s"> of the two pillars</span><span class="H8147 s">, and the two</span><span class="H7639 s"> wreaths</span><span class="H3680 s"> to cover</span><span class="H8147 s"> the two</span><span class="H1543 s"> pommels</span><span class="H3805 s"> of the chapiters</span><span class="H7218 s"> which <i>were</i> on the top</span><span class="H5982 s"> of the pillars</span>;</div>
<div id="v140.4.13"><span class="H702 s">And four</span><span class="H3967 s"> hundred</span><span class="H7416 s"> pomegranates</span><span class="H8147 s"> on the two</span><span class="H7639 s"> wreaths</span><span class="H8147 s">; two</span><span class="H2905 s"> rows</span><span class="H7416 s"> of pomegranates</span><span class="H259 s"> on each</span><span class="H7639 s"> wreath</span><span class="H3680 s">, to cover</span><span class="H8147 s"> the two</span><span class="H1543 s"> pommels</span><span class="H3805 s"> of the chapiters</span><span class="H6440 s"> which <i>were</i> upon</span><span class="H5982 s"> the pillars</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (upon: Heb. upon the face of)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.14"><span class="H6213 s">He made</span><span class="H4350 s"> also bases</span><span class="H3595 s">, and lavers</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H4350 s"> he upon the bases</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (lavers: or, caldrons)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.15"><span class="H259 s">One</span><span class="H3220 s"> sea</span><span class="H8147 s">, and twelve</span><span class="H6240 s"> †</span><span class="H1241 s"> oxen</span> under it.</div>
<div id="v140.4.16"><span class="H5518 s">The pots</span><span class="H3257 s"> also, and the shovels</span><span class="H4207 s">, and the fleshhooks</span><span class="H3627 s">, and all their instruments</span><span class="H2361 s">, did Huram</span><span class="H1 s"> his father</span><span class="H6213 s"> make</span><span class="H4428 s"> to king</span><span class="H8010 s"> Solomon</span><span class="H1004 s"> for the house</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H4838 s"> of bright</span><span class="H5178 s"> brass</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bright: Heb. made bright, or, scoured)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.17"><span class="H3603 s">In the plain</span><span class="H3383 s"> of Jordan</span><span class="H4428 s"> did the king</span><span class="H3332 s"> cast</span><span class="H5645 s"> them, in the clay</span><span class="H127 s"> ground</span><span class="H5523 s"> between Succoth</span><span class="H6868 s"> and Zeredathah</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (clay…: Heb. thicknesses of the ground)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.18"><span class="H8010 s">Thus Solomon</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H3627 s"> all these vessels</span><span class="H3966 s"> in great</span><span class="H7230 s"> abundance</span><span class="H4948 s">: for the weight</span><span class="H5178 s"> of the brass</span><span class="H2713 s"> could not be found out</span>.</div>
<div id="v140.4.19"><span class="H8010 s">And Solomon</span><span class="H6213 s"> made</span><span class="H3627 s"> all the vessels</span><span class="H1004 s"> that <i>were for</i> the house</span><span class="H430 s"> of God</span><span class="H2091 s">, the golden</span><span class="H4196 s"> altar</span><span class="H7979 s"> also, and the tables</span><span class="H3899 s"> whereon the shewbread</span><span class="H6440 s"> †</span> <i>was set</i>;</div>
<div id="v140.4.20"><span class="H4501 s">Moreover the candlesticks</span><span class="H5216 s"> with their lamps</span><span class="H1197 s">, that they should burn</span><span class="H4941 s"> after the manner</span><span class="H6440 s"> before</span><span class="H1687 s"> the oracle</span><span class="H5462 s">, of pure</span><span class="H2091 s"> gold</span>;</div>
<div id="v140.4.21"><span class="H6525 s">And the flowers</span><span class="H5216 s">, and the lamps</span><span class="H4457 s">, and the tongs</span><span class="H2091 s">, <i>made he of</i> gold</span><span class="H4357 s">, <i>and</i> that perfect</span><span class="H2091 s"> gold</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (perfect…: Heb. perfections of gold)</span></div>
<div id="v140.4.22"><span class="H4212 s">And the snuffers</span><span class="H4219 s">, and the basons</span><span class="H3709 s">, and the spoons</span><span class="H4289 s">, and the censers</span><span class="H5462 s">, <i>of</i> pure</span><span class="H2091 s"> gold</span><span class="H6607 s">: and the entry</span><span class="H1004 s"> of the house</span><span class="H6442 s">, the inner</span><span class="H1817 s"> doors</span><span class="H6944 s"> thereof for the most</span><span class="H6944 s"> holy</span><span class="H1817 s"> <i>place</i>, and the doors</span><span class="H1004 s"> of the house</span><span class="H1964 s"> of the temple</span><span class="H2091 s">, <i>were of</i> gold</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (basons: or, bowls)</span></div></div>
